##In March, nearly 8,000 shows were canceled, making it difficult to return to work in the first half of the year

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

Affected by the epidemic, the recent domestic performances again ushered in a wave of cancellation, delay peak. According to incomplete statistics from the China Performing Industry Association, nearly 8,000 performances were canceled or postponed in March in more than 20 provinces and cities across the country, with direct box office losses of more than 1 billion yuan in March. The Andy Lau concert, the Jonathan Lee Concert, the play Pride and Prejudice, the broken gold and other popular performances have been cancelled or postponed. Some people in the industry believe that this year's cultural performance industry or will enter the winter.

The performance industry continued to be suspended in March

After the outbreak, "cancel, delay, refund" has become a common vocabulary of many performing organizations. On January 22, Wuhan took the lead in announcing the suspension or cancellation of a number of cultural and travel activities, as well as the postponement or cancellation of a number of concerts and competitions in Wuhan.

On January 23, the Ministry of Culture and Tourism and the State Administration of Cultural Heritage issued a notice instructing local public cultural service agencies to strictly control the number and scale of mass cultural activities and strictly implement the system of reporting for approval or filing activities, to strictly examine the recent cultural and tourism exchange activities held at home and abroad, and to review the approved projects.

Subsequently, local performing organizations have responded, Beijing Poly Theatre, Beijing People's art, Tianqiao Theatre, Beijing Concert Hall, Mei Lanfang Theatre, Chang 'an grand theatre and other performances were announced to be suspended or cancelled.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Performance industry ushered in a "big test" in February, most of the various offline performances failed to meet the audience. According to data from the China Performing Industry Association, Incomplete Statistics show that about 20,000 shows were canceled or postponed in the first quarter of 2020, accounting for more than 80 percent of the total number of shows in the first quarter, resulting in direct box office losses of about 2.4 billion yuan, and estimated other losses of nearly 10 billion yuan.

Into March, the cancellation, extension and ushered in a wave of peaks. In the first half of February, the Shanghai Grand Theatre cancelled all performances and public cultural activities in March, including concerts, dance drama, drama, etc. . Shanghai Drama Arts Center cancels performances of "I love Peach Blossom" , "wilderness" and "no survivors" in March. On February 23, the National Centre for the Performing Arts issued a notice to cancel performances and related activities from March 1 to 31 and suspend visits.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Beijing Concert Hall, the Shanghai Oriental Arts Center and the Shanghai Symphony Orchestra have canceled or postponed all their concerts for March, while Jinghui Meng's theater studio and happy twist have canceled theater performances in several cities around the country.

Andy Lau cancelled 15 concerts after various parts of the show were affected

"The impact of this outbreak is very 'catastrophic' for the performing arts. Because the cultural performance industry is not a necessary part of people's lives, and there are too many restrictions on performing. Before it can be performed normally, it needs the right time, the right place, the right people and the right people to have a perfect performance."A relevant official of a cultural company in Beijing told Chinanews.com, this year's cultural performance industry may enter the winter.

They just released a new play last year. It was to be performed at the Poly Theater in the first half of this year. If it is decided to cancel or delay, the performance venues, actors, follow-up performances and so on will be re-coordinated.

"Pauly's venue is very popular and it's not easy to get a half-month venue in prime time. It took US nearly half a year to get the cast together to get it right. There are six shows still on the block that were supposed to open in, but have been put on hold,"the official said.

In the first half of this year, the adjustment of the show, a large proportion of the delay to be determined, Jonathan Lee, Han Hong, Eason Chan, Jolin Tsai, JJ Lin, Fish Leong, William Chan, Wu Tsing-Fong and many other stars of the concert is pending. Some of the delays are set for the second half of the year or even the 2021, when there is a good chance of a "crash" .

Breaking Gold, a play starring Zhang Guoli, Wang Gang and Zhang Tielin, was originally scheduled to open in March but has been postponed until the end of August. The Lithuanian National Theatre has postponed a tour of the play fatal Lokis to the 2021.

Some performances are not so lucky, due to schedule, venue, cost and so many issues can not be postponed, finally had to choose to cancel. Overseas artists such as THE PIXIES, THE Novembers, Sato, and THE French musical repertory concert tour to China have all been canceled.

This year, Andy Lau was due to hold the concert in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Wuhan, Hong Kong, etc. . Affected by the epidemic, nine events in Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou have been postponed. The Wuhan Concert in April was cancelled and the Hong Kong concert was cancelled due to venue and other reasons. In total, Andy Lau cancelled 15 concerts and postponed nine, with media estimates of the losses running into hundreds of millions of yuan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
China's entertainment industry returns to work, with online shows gaining popularity

"The first half of this year sees the concert the possibility not to be big. " Has the netizen forecast. In addition to performances in March, performances in April and may have been cancelled or postponed. The Guangzhou Opera House and the Shanghai Grand Theatre have cancelled or postponed all performances and public cultural activities for April. Canadian singer Avril Lavigne Lavigny has also announced that her Asian tour scheduled for April and May will be cancelled, including in Shenzhen, Shanghai, Foshan and Nanjing.

Compared with other industries, the prevention and control of the performing industry and return to work more difficult. On March 3, the city of Shanghai released the guidelines for the prevention and control of pneumonia in performing venues of the COVID-19, which stipulate the preparations before the resumption of performances and the measures for the prevention and control of the epidemic after the resumption, for example, the implementation of real-name admission system, misalignment of each performance out of tickets, seat rate control within 50% , cancel pre-performance and post-performance interactive activities.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Some performance agencies believe that the current situation also means that no performance companies can really resume work, for the performance companies can not achieve 100% sales, profit is minimal. In addition, the audience's psychological needs to be built, the case after all clear, we would also like to see a performance, these are unknown.

Face this"big test", the answer sheet that everybody gives also is different. Only the traditional performance offline mode met challenges, cloud performances, cloud concerts and other popular. The National Centre for the Performing Arts has launched the online grand theater, which streams daily videos of performances. Forbidden City Concert Hall launches "listening to concerts online" to share videos of performances by famous artists. Poly Theater launched "Poly Cloud Theater" , introduced drama, concerts, master class, literature and art war epidemic four plates.

In addition, modern sky launched the "curtilage strawberry" cloud music festival has also triggered a new trend. Japanese Music Master Ryuichi Sakamoto's cloud concert recently, the number of online viewers reached more than 3 million.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"House Strawberry" cloud music festival poster

Not all shows can be replaced by cloud services, but for the performers, they can walk on two legs, both online and offline, explore more profit models, and diversify their development, it may also be an important way to reduce risk now and in the future.

Source: Chinanews.com, by Yuan Xiuyue
